President Barack Obama has announced his intent to nominate three individuals to key administration posts. Richard Howorth is nominated for Member, Board of Directors of the Tennessee Valley Authority. Howorth is the owner of Square Books, a bookstore in Mississippi, and has served as the Mayor of Oxford, Mississippi. Lisa Monaco is nominated for Assistant Attorney General for National Security at the Department of Justice. She is currently the Principal Associate Deputy Attorney General and has previously worked for the FBI and as an Assistant U.S. Attorney. Myrna Pérez is nominated for Commissioner of the Election Assistance Commission. Pérez is currently Senior Counsel at the Brennan Center for Justice and has worked on voting rights issues. She has also served as a policy analyst at the United States Government Accountability Office.